						               													<description>Seven is a set collecting game based on 7 sets of 7 cards, 17 special cards, and 4 Jokers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Seven is turn-based and everybody starts with 10 cards each at the beginning.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rest of the cards are placed face-down in a pile on the table and every player must pick up a card at the end of their turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The objective is simply to collect as many of the seven sets as you can. You can collect sets by asking other players for cards during your turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are 17 special cards (marked with gold and black stars) and 14 of them have good functions that can give you an advantage in the game. The other 3 are negative and it's simply bad luck if you encounter one.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Jokers enable you to lie once when another player asks you for a card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Source: the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
